{"title":"Combined feed","url":"https://Vinnl.github.io/feeds/all.xml","elements":[{"title":"Tom Scutt (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that a Tony Award–winning set by <b><a href=\"/wiki/Tom_Scutt\" title=\"Tom Scutt\">Tom Scutt</a></b> <i>(pictured)</i> has the audience entering through a side entrance to make a \"descent into the <a href=\"/wiki/Cabaret_(musical)\" title=\"Cabaret (musical)\">cabaret</a>\"?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tom_Scutt","retrieved":1782635539205},{"title":"Wyoming Supreme Court censured a judge (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that the <b><a href=\"/wiki/In_re_Neely\" title=\"In re Neely\">Wyoming Supreme Court censured a judge</a></b> for announcing that she would not marry same-sex couples?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/In_re_Neely","retrieved":1782635539222},{"title":"pretext for war (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that the image of Christ on gold coins was a <b><a href=\"/wiki/Battle_of_Sebastopolis\" title=\"Battle of Sebastopolis\">pretext for war</a></b>?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Battle_of_Sebastopolis","retrieved":1782635539222},{"title":"Syed Abid Husain (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <b><a href=\"/wiki/Syed_Abid_Husain\" title=\"Syed Abid Husain\">Syed Abid Husain</a></b><span class=\"nowrap\">'s</span> play <i>The Veil of Ignorance</i> explores social discourse on access to modern education by Indian women?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syed_Abid_Husain","retrieved":1782635539224},{"title":"her third album (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that Mary Lattimore recorded <b><a href=\"/wiki/Hundreds_of_Days\" title=\"Hundreds of Days\">her third album</a></b> in a barn?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hundreds_of_Days","retrieved":1782635539224},{"title":"Aaron Mahnke (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <i><a href=\"/wiki/Lore_(podcast)\" title=\"Lore (podcast)\">Lore</a></i> podcaster <b><a href=\"/wiki/Aaron_Mahnke\" title=\"Aaron Mahnke\">Aaron Mahnke</a></b> thought to make the show after his history and folklore PDFs made for fans of his thriller novels became too large to maintain?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aaron_Mahnke","retrieved":1782635539225},{"title":"government officials (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that during the Ming dynasty, prospective <b><a href=\"/wiki/Government_of_the_Ming_dynasty\" title=\"Government of the Ming dynasty\">government officials</a></b> needed to write an <a href=\"/wiki/Eight-legged_essay\" title=\"Eight-legged essay\">eight-legged essay</a> about the <a href=\"/wiki/Four_Books_and_Five_Classics#Four_Books\" title=\"Four Books and Five Classics\">Four Books</a> in Confucianism for their examinations?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government_of_the_Ming_dynasty","retrieved":1782635539226},{"title":"a New York State TV station (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that the first studios of <b><a href=\"/wiki/WXXI-TV\" title=\"WXXI-TV\">a New York State TV station</a></b> had floors that were so uneven that a camera could wobble as it moved?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WXXI-TV","retrieved":1782635539228},{"title":"the 1990s Wired style guide (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <b><a href=\"/wiki/Wired_Style\" title=\"Wired Style\">the 1990s <i>Wired</i> style guide</a></b> defines <i>WTFIGO</i> and <i>userid</i>, but not <i>WTF</i> or <i>username</i><span style=\"padding-left:0.15em;\">?</span>","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wired_Style","retrieved":1782635539229},{"title":"Destination of the Month (Wikivoyage recommendations)","contents":"<span class=\"mw-empty-elt\" about=\"#mwt8\" typeof=\"mw:Transclusion\" id=\"mwIQ\" data-mw=\"{&quot;parts&quot;:[{&quot;template&quot;:{&quot;target&quot;:{&quot;wt&quot;:&quot;banner&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:&quot;./Template:Banner&quot;},&quot;params&quot;:{&quot;direction&quot;:{&quot;wt&quot;:&quot;left&quot;},&qu